In a series of remarks made on June 8, 2018, President Trump discussed a variety of topics, including the upcoming release of the Comey report, unfair trade practices by Canada, Mexico, and the European Union, his preparations for the Kim summit, the recent leak of classified information, the death of Anthony Bourdain, the G7 summit, potential pardons, the NFL national anthem protests, and his views on the media and freedom of the press. He also mentioned his wife's recent surgery and his admiration for Muhammad Ali and Dennis Rodman.